  "prompt": "What's a good uninstalled for windows?",
  "response": "There are several good uninstallers for Windows that can help you remove unwanted programs and clean up leftover files. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Revo Uninstaller**:\n   - Offers thorough scanning for leftover files, folders, and registry entries.\n   - Provides various uninstall modes, including built-in uninstaller, safe mode, and advanced mode.\n   - Includes additional tools like junk file cleaner and autorun manager.\n\n2. **IObit Uninstaller**:\n   - Provides deep cleaning of leftover files and registry entries.\n   - Features batch uninstallation and easy removal of bundled software and browser extensions.\n   - Includes additional tools such as Windows updates removal and software updater.\n\n3. **Geek Uninstaller**:\n   - Lightweight and portable, no installation required.\n   - Offers force removal for stubborn programs.\n   - Provides detailed information about installed programs and supports batch uninstallation.\n\n4. **Advanced Uninstaller PRO**:\n   - Thorough removal of programs and leftover files.\n   - Includes additional tools like registry cleaner, startup manager, and file shredder.\n   - Offers a user-friendly interface and detailed monitoring of installations.\n\n5. **CCleaner**:\n   - Although primarily a system optimization tool, it includes a basic uninstaller.\n   - Provides additional features like registry cleaner, disk cleanup, and privacy protection.\n   - Offers a straightforward interface and regular updates.\n\nEach of these tools has its own strengths and additional features, so you may want to try a few to see which best suits your needs.",
